---
description: Git commit messages and PR text must not include tool attribution footers
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git messages: no attribution footers

- Do **not** append automated vendor or editor attribution lines to **any** git commit message, amend message, rebase message, tag message, or PR description you draft or suggest (including extra `Co-authored-by:` trailers unless the user explicitly asks for a real co-author).
- Messages must end with real content only: subject, body, and trailers the user requested. No marketing or tool footers unless the user explicitly asks for them.
